## .NET 9 Specific Practices

### Use Modern C# Features for Simplicity

```csharp
// ❌ Verbose
public class GetUserResponse
{
    public string Name { get; set; }
    public string Email { get; set; }
}

// ✅ Simple — record does the same with less
public record GetUserResponse(string Name, string Email);
```

```csharp
// ❌ Nested null checks
if (user != null && user.Address != null && user.Address.City != null)

// ✅ Null-conditional + pattern matching
if (user?.Address?.City is string city)
```

```csharp
// ❌ Traditional switch with fallthrough risk
switch (status)
{
    case "Active": return HandleActive();
    case "Inactive": return HandleInactive();
    default: throw new ArgumentException();
}

// ✅ Switch expression — exhaustive, concise
return status switch
{
    "Active" => HandleActive(),
    "Inactive" => HandleInactive(),
    _ => throw new UnreachableException()
};
```

### Naming as Documentation

```csharp
// ❌ Needs a comment to understand
var d = DateTime.Now - u.CDate; // days since creation
if (d.TotalDays > 30) { ... }

// ✅ Self-explanatory
var daysSinceCreation = DateTime.UtcNow - user.CreatedAt;
if (daysSinceCreation.TotalDays > 30) { ... }
```

```csharp
// ❌ Unclear method
public List<User> Get(bool a, int t) { ... }

// ✅ Name tells the story
public List<User> GetActiveUsersByOrganization(int organizationId) { ... }
```

### Service & Controller Practices

```csharp
// ❌ Fat controller doing business logic
[HttpPost]
public async Task<IActionResult> CreateUser(CreateUserRequest request)
{
    var existing = await _db.Users.FirstOrDefaultAsync(u => u.Email == request.Email);
    if (existing != null) return Conflict();
    var user = new User { Name = request.Name, Email = request.Email };
    _db.Users.Add(user);
    await _db.SaveChangesAsync();
    return Ok(user);
}

// ✅ Thin controller, logic in service
[HttpPost]
public async Task<IActionResult> CreateUser(CreateUserRequest request)
{
    var result = await _userService.CreateUser(request);
    return result.Match<IActionResult>(
        success => Ok(success),
        conflict => Conflict(conflict.Message)
    );
}
```

### Dependency Injection

```csharp
// ❌ Newing up dependencies
public class UserService
{
    private readonly DatabaseContext _db = new DatabaseContext();
}

// ✅ Constructor injection
public class UserService(DatabaseContext db, ILogger<UserService> logger) : IUserService
{
    // primary constructor — fields are the parameters themselves
}
```

### Guard Clauses over Nesting

```csharp
// ❌ Deep nesting
public async Task<User> GetUser(int id)
{
    if (id > 0)
    {
        var user = await _db.Users.FindAsync(id);
        if (user != null)
        {
            if (user.IsActive)
            {
                return user;
            }
        }
    }
    return null;
}

// ✅ Guard clauses — flat, readable
public async Task<User?> GetActiveUser(int id)
{
    if (id <= 0)
        throw new ArgumentException("Id must be positive", nameof(id));

    var user = await _db.Users.FindAsync(id);
    if (user is null)
        return null;

    if (!user.IsActive)
        return null;

    return user;
}
```

