## When to Refactor

- **Rule of Three** — First time: just do it. Second time: wince but do it. Third time: refactor.
- **Before adding a feature** — Clean the area you're about to change.
- **When fixing a bug** — If the code around the bug is messy, clean it first. Bugs hide in messy code.
- **During code review** — The last chance to catch smells before they reach main.

---

## Checklist Before Every PR

1. No method longer than ~20 lines without good reason
2. No class doing more than one job
3. No magic strings or numbers
4. No copy-pasted logic
5. No comments that restate what the code does
6. All names are self-explanatory
7. No deep nesting (max 2 levels)
8. No unused code
9. Guard clauses used instead of nested ifs
10. Records used for DTOs and value objects
